> > While it "might" have a 914 engine most likely it is just the pancake
> > which shares many of the same design features as the 914 engine. There
> > is most likely an easier way to check, but the way I know is that on

> > Many people try to distinguish the upright engine (i.e. beetles &
> > older busses) and the T4 (or T2) engine which has a fan on the end of
> > the crankshaft, this way.

and just to add to the confusion the T3 engine is a T1/2 engine with the
fan on the end of the crankshaft....
> 
> The easy difference is in the engine case- The 914 dipstick is on top
> next to the breather and the bus-type oil filler location is a closed
> casting.
> The fan housing is also closed at the dipstick and won't work for bus.

well again not so cut and dried the "real" T4 engine in the 411/412 sedans
will also have the closed off end and dipstick on the top...

about the only "Real" way to know for sure is the engine serial number

